<HEADLINE>
FT  06 DEC 94 / UK Company News: CRT ahead sharply to Pounds 1.29m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER PEARSE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CRT Group, the training and recruitment group which bought Systems Resources
in August, lifted pre-tax profits from a restated Pounds 472,000 to Pounds
1.29m in the six months to October 31.
The shares eased 2p to 82p.
Operating profits advanced to Pounds 1.67m (Pounds 1.64m) after a Pounds
220,000 contribution from the acquisition. Last year's figure, however,
included losses of Pounds 635,000 from the discontinued Doctus Consulting
Europe, now sold to management. Group turnover grew 30 per cent to Pounds
29.2m (Pounds 22.4m) including Pounds 5.2m from Systems Resources.
In recruitment, turnover rose 90 per cent to Pounds 18.5m (Pounds 9.75m) and
operating profits more than doubled to Pounds 964,000 (Pounds 467,000).
Stripping out the effect of the acquisition, which made a two-month
contribution, the rises in turnover and operating profits were 37 and 59 per
cent respectively.
In training, turnover grew to Pounds 10.5m (Pounds 9.46m) but operating
profits fell to Pounds 1.67m (Pounds 1.85m). Explaining the fall, Mr Karl
Chapman, group chief executive, cited increased weighting to students
completing courses in the second half, development of the Link Training
Multimedia Learning Centre programme in schools, and investment in Link and
Pitman.
The group's second-half bias would be more pronounced this year, Mr Chapman
said, because of the acquisition, the general improvement in the recruitment
market and continuing weighting of that market to the second six months.
There was a Pounds 300,000 integration and restructuring charge, and Mr
Chapman said the total charge would not exceed Pounds 650,000 for the year.
Earnings rose to 1.42p (0.56p) per share and the interim dividend is raised
to 0.85p (0.75p).
</TEXT>
