<HEADLINE>
FT  06 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Overseas side helps Faber Prest rise 32%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GEOFF DYER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A strong performance from its industrial services division, particularly
overseas, helped Faber Prest to announce a 32 per cent increase in pre-tax
profits.
The rise in profits at the industrial and distribution services group, from
Pounds 5.03m to Pounds 6.63m for the year ended September 30, was achieved
on turnover up 15 per cent at Pounds 79.5m (Pounds 69.5m).
Underlying growth in turnover on continuing activities was 13 per cent to
Pounds 74.7m (Pounds 66.1m) giving operating profits of Pounds 5.78m (Pounds
5.35m), an increase of 8 per cent. There were exceptional profits of Pounds
595,000, compared with net losses of Pounds 42,000.
Expenditure on acquisitions was Pounds 5.4m (Pounds 500,000) and capital
expenditure doubled to Pounds 7.4m (Pounds 3.5m). The group raised Pounds
8.5m in a 1-for-4 rights issue in July.
Mr Roger Feaviour, chief executive, said that this pace of expansion would
continue.
Operating profits from industrial services, principally slag recovery and
utilisation, increased 31 per cent to Pounds 4.33m (Pounds 3.31m).
The distribution division, which provides logistics services, increased
profits by 5 per cent to Pounds 1.84m (Pounds 1.75m) on sales of Pounds
24.6m (Pounds 21.3m).
Earnings per share rose 32 per cent to 43.7p (33.3p). The proposed final
dividend is 10p (9p) making a total of 15.5p (14p).
</TEXT>
