FT  06 DEC 94 / UK Company News: AB Foods buys flour producer
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JAMES WHITTINGTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Associated British Foods, the milling, baking, and sugar group has bought
Allinson, the UK's leading producer of stoneground flour, from Booker for
Pounds 6.7m in cash together with Pounds 1.5m in repayment of inter-group
loans.
ABF is one of the biggest consumers of stoneground flour in the UK and has
been using the Allinson brandname under licence for the past 12 years.
Mr Garry Weston, chairman of ABF, said the purchase will consolidate the
group's position in the wholemeal bread market. 'We have been spending
considerable sums of money promoting and developing the brandname and we
wanted the security of owning it,' he said.
The disposal of Allinson comes as part of a restructuring at Bookers
initiated 12 months ago.
