<HEADLINE>
FT  06 DEC 94 / Fall reported in business failures
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The number of business failures in the third quarter of this year fell to
its lowest level since 1989, a business survey has found.
The survey, conducted by Trade Indemnity, the credit management group, says
that there were 784 business failures in the third quarter of this year.
This was 5 per cent lower than in the second quarter, and 33 per cent lower
than the same period a year ago.
However, Trade Indemnity pointed out that the fall in business failures
appeared to be slowing, with some regions, such as the north-east, west
Midlands and East Anglia, recording a rise in business failures between the
second and third quarters of this year.
