<HEADLINE>
FT  06 DEC 94 / Local polls hit Berlusconi
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROME
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Italian local elections over the weekend increased the fragility of the
right-wing government and turned the spotlight on the possibility of a
centre-left coalition. Centre-left opposition alliances won the mayoral
races in the run-off for four out of six regional capitals, two of the
regional councils and a majority of the small local administrations being
contested. Prime minister Mr Silvio Berlusconi's Forza Italia movement
showed signs of losing momentum and in the south the neo-fascist
MSI/National Alliance surprised every commentator by the poor performance in
its heartland.
